*VICTOR (V.O.)
To say from where I harvested the ruthless remedy... would be poetic-perhaps even boastful- but I harvested it all the same...*

CAMERA PULLS BACK to reveal Young Victor walking away from the black granite stone of his Mother's GRAVE.

INT. FRANKENSTEIN VILLA - KITCHEN - BLUE DAWN

Young Victor puts on his MOTHER'S GLOVES as he boils the lichen and some chemicals and powders from his father's study.

                                   (CONTINUED) CONTINUED:

*VICTOR (V.O.)
It yielded its essence- just like my mother had relinquished hers to the ground... the plant had sapped her spirit and nourished her way out of the earth... to me.
